  "label": "Glasseam Hollow",
  "description": "Glasseam Hollow is a basalt cave cut through by a black, vitrified seam that runs like a frozen lightning-strike along the walls and ceiling. The floor slopes into a shallow basin of ash-fine grit and slag pebbles, where melt-glossed stone holds the cold with a persistent damp chill. Mineral efflorescence clings in pale crusts to fracture lines, catching the peak’s bruise-hued ambient light as a faint, oil-sheened glimmer. The chamber’s air remains heavy with metallic tang and stale dust, carrying the muffled resonance of distant rock stress through Sablecrown Peak’s rift-scarred mass.",
